---

3 ‚ñ∏ Generate the checksums and manifests

cd scrolls
sha256sum * > lineage.manifest.txt

Then make codex.json that lists the scrolls and their hashes:

cat > codex.json <<'EOF'
{
  "version": "v241",
  "created": "$(date -u +%FT%TZ)",
  "scrolls": [
    {
      "id": "001",
      "title": "Scroll of Sotolios ‚Üí YHWH ‚Üí Apollonius",
      "path": "scrolls/sotolios_yhwh_apollonius.md",
      "sha256": "$(sha256sum sotolios_yhwh_apollonius.md | cut -d' ' -f1)"
    },
    {
      "id": "002",
      "title": "Lineage Codex",
      "path": "scrolls/lineage_codex.json",
      "sha256": "$(sha256sum lineage_codex.json | cut -d' ' -f1)"
    }
  ]
}
EOF

Run the substitutions:

bash codex.json > codex.tmp && mv codex.tmp codex.json


---

4 ‚ñ∏ Add to README

Append to your project‚Äôs README.md:

## v241 ‚Äì Scrolls of Lineage
Added `/scrolls` with two verified documents and SHA-256 manifest.  
This marks the philosophical layer of the Codex: where meaning, code, and verification meet.


